Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Navy Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected the command of Navy Unit 152 of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Being guided by the commander of the unit, he went round a room devoted to the education in revolutionary history, a room devoted to the unit's history and a room devoted to preservation and education in slogan-bearing trees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing the relics and data associated with revolutionary history, he recalled with deep emotion the days of President Kim Il Sung's leadership over the building of navy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Navy of the KPA could grow to be invincible forces under the wise leadership and deep care of the President who devoted all his energies to building and strengthening the naval forces until the last moments of his life, he said, adding: His immortal revolutionary exploits for the building of the Juche-oriented navy will remain long in the history of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that those trees bearing slogans written during the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle are a precious asset of the Korean revolution, he stressed the need to intensify the education of servicepersons through the slogans and thus arm them more firmly with the revolutionary idea of the WPK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He dropped in at an operation command room to learn about the unit's performance of duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled by the unit to increase its combat capability in every way, satisfied to learn that the servicepersons of the unit are carrying out their guard duties in a responsible manner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He made the rounds of the servicepersons' hall, a library and other entertainment and cultural and educational facilities to learn about how the political work is being conducted among seamen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All units have successfully built libraries and minutely organized their service, thus markedly boosting the soldiers' zeal for reading, he noted, adding that the habit of reading books established in the whole army is another praiseworthy trait created by the KPA in the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After visiting the Hero Ri Kwang Su Company, he said it is good for the servicepersons of the unit to make their youth worthwhile with arms. He urged all servicepersons to become heroes in the new century by carrying forward the soul of the revolutionary forerunners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he went round a mess hall, a kitchen, a non-staple food store, a mushroom cultivation room and other supply service facilities of the unit modernly built to suit the characteristic features of the seamen. He appreciated the efforts made by the commanding officers of the unit, expressing satisfaction over the fact that they have provided the soldiers with good living conditions, bearing deep in mind the teaching of the President that supply service is at once a political work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He looked round the exterior and interior of the soldiers' health complex newly built by the unit and indicated tasks to be fulfilled by it to manage and operate it and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to show special care for the living of the seamen as they live in the rough sea all the year round, he called on all commanding officers to show warm love for the soldiers and look after them with paternal care so that they may not feel even the slightest inconvenience in their living.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit.

Spokesman for DPRK Foreign Ministry on DPRK-U.S. Talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry gave the following answer to the question put by KCNA on Wednesday as regards the DPRK-U.S. talks held in Singapore: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-U.S. talks were held in Singapore on April 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks had an in-depth discussion on issues arising in implementing the October 3 agreement of the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result of the talks a consensus was reached on the U.S. measure to make political compensation and the nuclear declaration essential for winding up the implementation of the agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent Singapore agreement fully proved the effectiveness of the DPRK-U.S. talks.
 We will follow the fulfillment of the commitments of those countries  participating in the six-party talks.

Session of DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The Sixth Session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea was held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the session were deputies to the SPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Also on hand as observers were officials of party, armed forces and power organs, social organizations, ministries and national institutions and officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and media. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The session discussed the following agenda items: "1. On the review of the work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 96 (2007) and its tasks for Juche 97 (2008)" and "2. On the results of the implementation of the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 96 (2007) and its state budget for Juche 97 (2008)" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet, noted in the report on the first agenda item that last year a new phase was brought in the building of an economic power to increase the gross industrial output, major tasks of the 5-year plan for the development of the nation's science and technology ending in 2007 were carried out, and signal achievements were made in culture building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter stressed that the main tasks in the field of economy for this year is to boost the basic industries, the pilot sectors of the national economy, so as to make a breakthrough in building an economic power and steadily push ahead with the technical modernization of the national economy while decisively solving the food and consumer goods problems to bring a substantial improvement in the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, in his report on the second agenda item said that last year the plan for the state budgetary revenue was carried out at 100.2 per cent, a 6.1 per cent increase in revenue over the previous year and the plan for state budgetary expenditure at 101.7 per cent and 15.7 per cent of the total state budgetary expenditure was disbursed as military spending and a large amount of fund was allocated for the various fields of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state budgetary revenue for this year is planned to grow four per cent over last year, he said, adding: This year the state budgetary expenditure will show an increase of 2.5 per cent over last year and much portion of the state budget be invested in the development of the national economy and the improvement of the standard of people's living and 15.8 per cent of the total state budgetary expenditure allocated for national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the session said that the work of the Cabinet and the implementation of the state budget last year were properly reviewed and settled, and expressed full support and approval of the reports made on the two agenda items as clear tasks for this year were proposed and the state budget properly shaped. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the session, SPA decision "On approving the report on the work of the DPRK Cabinet and the results of the implementation of the state budget for Juche 96 (2007)" and SPA ordinance "On the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 97 (2008)" were adopted with unanimous approval of the deputies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the session Deputy Kang Nung Su, vice-chairman of the SPA, was recalled.

Report on DPRK Cabinet's Work Last Year and Its Tasks for This Year 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Premier of the Cabinet Kim Yong Il, deputy to the Supreme People's Assembly, delivered a report on the work done by the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 96 (2007) and its tasks for Juche 97 (2008) at the 6th session of the 11th SPA held Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The report said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last year was the year of struggle and advance in which the political and military might of the DPRK was fully demonstrated all over the world and a fresh phase brought about in building an economic power under the unique Songun revolutionary leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Important political events including the grand political festivals commemorating the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung and the 75th anniversary of the Korean People's Army and the election of deputies to the local power bodies helped strikingly demonstrate the solidity of the ideology and traditions of the DPRK, the indomitable will and the militancy of all the servicepersons and people single-mindedly united around the party and consolidate the DPRK government as firm as a rock. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Precious successes were achieved last year to demonstrate the economic potential of the country and the inexhaustible creative ability of our people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thousands of major factories and enterprises across the country overfulfilled their national economy plan, taking the country as a whole.  The gross industrial output swelled, the foundation of the self-supporting national economy gained in scope and strength and the major projects of the five-year plan for the development of national science and technology ending in 2007 were carried out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The educational field witnessed progress in modernizing the educational institutions at all levels and improving the quality of education and signal successes in the fields of public health, culture and arts and sports. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK set a grandiose target to open up without fail the gate of a great prosperous powerful nation in 2012, the centenary of birth of the President, by staging a general offensive from this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main tasks before the economic field this year is to bolster the pilot sectors, basic industries of the national economy, giving top priority to the work for ensuring the increase of the country's defence capability true to the Party's line of economic construction in the era of Songun, and thus ensure the advance in the building of an economic power. It is also the main thrust of the field to continue vigorously pushing forward the technological updating of the national economy and, at the same time, decisively solve the problems of food and consumer goods on the people's living-first principle in order to substantially improve the people's living standard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will make a fresh leap forward and progress in all fields under the uplifted militant slogan of the Party "Glorify This Year of the 60th Anniversary of the Founding of the DPRK as a Year of Historical Turn Which Will Go Down in the History of the Country!", thus significantly boosting the gross industrial output value. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year the Cabinet will channel all human and material resources of the country into bolstering the fields of power, coal and metal industries and railway transportation, taking a firm hold on the pilot sectors, basic industrial fields of the national economy, as the lifeline of the socialist economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cabinet will rejuvenate the geological prospecting and the production at key industries including mining, machine-building, chemical and building materials industries and forestry and accelerate the technological updating on the basis of the existing foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an important task before the Cabinet this year, the 60th anniversary of the DPRK, to abide by the people's living-first principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  We will comprehensively introduce high-yielding rice and maize seeds on the principle of the right crop on the right soil and the proper crop in the right season, widely disseminate and generalize the advanced agro-technique and farming methods and intensify the self-farming movement, true to the Party's policy of agricultural revolution to make great progress in solving the people's problem of food at any cost this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will vigorously push forward the waterway projects and land development and let all the fields of national economy produce and ensure farming materials in a responsible manner and encourage the whole country to render labor and material assistance to rural areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will boost the production of meat, eggs and aquatic products and substantially operate the existing fish breeding centers to enable the people to fully benefit from them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will mass-produce quality consumer goods by operating the light industrial factories in full capacity and continue pushing forward the work to build new production bases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will spruce up the hospitals at different levels as required by the new century, improve the production and supply of medicines and medical apparatus and make sure that all the popular policies including the system of social insurance, the system of accommodating working people at sanatoria and rest homes and the system of preferential treatment of disabled soldiers are properly enforced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will speed up the construction of monumental edifices of the times, organize and undertake the construction of Pyongyang City in a bold and big way and build more houses in urban and rural areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From this year we will start implementing the new five-year plan for the development of national science and technology ending in 2012. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will systematically increase the state investment in this field and let the scientists and technicians increase their responsibility and role to successfully carry out the assignments under the plan and thus put the country's science and technology on an advanced level in the shortest possible period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the present, we will make sure that all the fields of national economy carry out the first-year tasks of the plan without fail this year, establish the production system based on science and technology at the factories and enterprises and, at the same time, exert state efforts for the development of the IT industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will thoroughly establish Juche in external economic relations with other countries, energetically expand the export of goods of the second- and third-stage processing by use of the locally available resources and on the basis of indigenous technology and conduct diversified and multilateral trade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an important task facing the Cabinet to steadily improve the guidance and administration of the socialist economic management and round off it our own way. It is also an issue of key importance as it awaits an urgent solution in building an economic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to concentrate the economic work on the Cabinet and develop the nation's economy under a long-term plan on the basis of a scientific strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will continue directing big efforts to building socialist culture to train a large number of able intellectuals capable of doing their shares in building a great prosperous powerful nation this year, too. We will, at the same time, see to it that more literary and art works reflecting the stirring reality in the era of Songun are created and efforts are focused on the preparations for exalting the honor of the country by winning gold medals in the 29th Olympics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called upon all officials to stand in the van of the drive for building an economic power and give the fullest play to the mental and creative power of the producer masses and thus work fresh miracles and innovations in production and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need for all the people to work hard to greet the 60th anniversary of the DPRK with shining victories and bring earlier the day when a great prosperous powerful socialist nation will appear on this land that remains highly dignified thanks to Songun.

Report on Implementation of State Budget for Last Year and State Budget for 2008 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Vice-Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Ro Tu Chol, deputy to the Supreme People's Assembly (SPA), delivered a report on the results of the implementation of the DPRK state budget for Juche 96 (2007) and its state budget for Juche 97 (2008) at the sixth session of the 11th SPA held on Wednesday. 
 According to the report, the last year's plan for state budgetary revenue was carried out at 100.2 per cent, a 6.1 per cent increase in revenue over the previous year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The plan for local budgetary revenue was carried out at 110.9 per cent, thus ensuring the planned disbursement with local income and channeling enormous fund into the national budget. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last year's plan for state budgetary expenditure was carried out at 101.7 per cent as unexpected happenings required the additional spending of a huge amount of funds in the course of its implementation including the funds for eradicating the aftermath of flood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The expenditure for agriculture in the state budget for last year showed an 8.5 per cent growth and that for light industry remarkably increased as compared with the previous year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government made a greater allocation of funds than plan for enforcing popular policies under the conditions where the national economy has not yet been reenergized, taking the nation's economy as a whole. This enabled the people to receive ample state benefits such as free medical care, free education, social insurance and social security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year 15.7 per cent of the total state budgetary expenditure was disbursed as military spending. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state budgetary revenue and expenditure for this year have been shaped on the principle of increasing the budgetary revenue to the maximum and reducing the expenditure for non-productive fields as much as possible by tapping all reserves and potentials in all fields and units of the national economy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year's plan for state budgetary revenue is expected to grow 4 per cent over last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revenue from the profits of state enterprises is expected to go up 4.7 per cent over last year, that from the profits of cooperative organizations 0.4 per cent, that from the fixed asset depreciation 2.6 per cent, that from rent of real estate 3.1 per cent and that from social insurance 1.1 per cent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year's state budgetary expenditure is expected to show a 2.5 per cent increase over last year and its plan has been shaped in such a way as to decisively bolster the pilot sectors, basic industrial sectors of national economy and bring about a landmark turn in improving the people's living standard, while making sustained efforts to increase the defence capability of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 15.8 per cent of the total state budgetary expenditure for this year will be allocated for national defence.  49.8 per cent more than last year will go to the fields of power, coal and metal industries and railway transportation and the expenditure for agriculture is expected to go up 5.5 per cent and that for science and technology 6.1 per cent  over last year. A huge financial disbursement will also be made for the light industry, capital construction and land administration and city management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state budgetary expenditure for enforcing the popular policies will swell 1.7 per cent over last year.  4.2 per cent more fund than last year will be disbursed for education and financial allocation for public health will increase 5.9 per cent to steadily enforce social policies such as the system of universal compulsory free education, the system of free medical care, the system of social insurance, the system of accommodating working people at sanatoria and rest homes and the system of preferential treatment of disabled soldiers. The DPRK will thus give full play to the popular nature and advantages of its socialist state budget. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is expected that the government will send a large amount of educational aid fund and stipends to the children of Koreans in Japan this year, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that it is the most important way for successfully implementing the state budget for this year to improve the economic and financial management in such a way as to gain the greatest possible profits, while strictly adhering to the socialist principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for successfully carrying out the state budget to glorify this year of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK as a year of a historical turn which will go down in the history of the country.

Deputies to SPA Enjoy Concert 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly who are attending the 6th Session of the 11th SPA, appreciated a concert of the Mansudae Art Troupe at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre on Wednesday on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage of the concert, which began with female vocal solo and chorus "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il", were such colorful numbers as male vocal solo "Thunder on Jong Il Peak", female folk solo "Longing for the General", female chorus "Song of Mangyongdae", violin solo "To the Road of Decisive Battle", mixed quintet "My Motherland under the Songun Policy" and chorus "General on a Galloping White Horse".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers ardently sang of the undying exploits of leader Kim Jong Il who has put the dignity and the strength of the DPRK on the highest level with his great Songun idea and guidance while ushering in the great heyday of prosperity unprecedented in the history of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The audience deeply felt again great happiness of being the nation of the sun that has covered the road of victory and glory while being blessed with illustrious leaders generation after generation.

Moves to Reinforce U.S.-S. Korea "Military Alliance" under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The U.S. defense secretary and the south Korean "minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade" were reported to have exchanged their views on the orientation of developing the U.S.-south Korea "military alliance" and the pending issues related to the "alliance relations" at their talks. What merits attention here is that the U.S. reiterated its support to the proposal for elevating the position of south Korea to the same level as the NATO's in purchasing U.S.-made weapons, crying out for the "tightened alliance" with south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today observes that this is a revelation of the U.S. sinister intention to sharply expand the scope of its delivery of weapons to south Korea and further tighten the U.S.-south Korea military nexus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. is keen to build a missile shield in south Korea, while contemplating giving south Korea the same status as the NATO's in the purchase of U.S.-made weapons. Lurking behind this scenario is a criminal intention to knock into shape a NATO-type new military bloc for aggression in Northeast Asia and realize its wild ambition for domination at any cost through that mechanism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is set to further tighten the "military alliance" with south Korea and put into practice its plan for creating a new military bloc by using the fictitious "threat" from the DPRK as a playing card. To this end, the U.S. is becoming vociferous about "threat" from the DPRK and pushing forward the moves to bolster the combat capability of its forces in south Korea and modernize the south Korean forces under the watchword of "security" in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military moves to knock a new military bloc into shape in Northeast Asia including its plan to plug south Korea into the moves to build a missile shield are anti-peace actions contrary to the trend of the times. They only escalate the military tension and further increase the danger of war on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. truly wants peace and security in Northeast Asia including the peninsula, it should immediately give up the above-mentioned moves.

Anti-DPRK Smear Campaign over "Human Rights" Slammed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The Lee Myung Bak group's anti-DPRK smear campaign over "human rights" is an intolerable challenge to the DPRK system and a deliberate political provocation aimed at inciting antagonism and distrust among fellow countrymen and deteriorating the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
There has been no "human rights issue" and it can never exist in the DPRK where the exploitation of man by man was brought to an end long ago and there are no legal and institutional factors of abusing "human rights". The Lee group's talk about "human rights issue" is a revelation of their ignorance of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is ridiculous and disgusting, indeed, for the group of traitors to say anything about someone's "human rights issue" as it is beset with the worst human rights issues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
There are differing ideologies and systems in the north and the south. Proceeding from the viewpoint of national reconciliation, unity and reunification, the DPRK has maintained the stand to develop the inter-Korean relations on the basis of leaving those ideologies and systems in the north and the south as they are and tolerating them. The three principles -- independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity --agreed upon and published by the north and the south serve as inviolable basic principles for developing the inter-Korean relations under any circumstances. Fully embodied in the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, a programme for implementing it, the principles serve as a powerful engine for steering the era of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the ulterior aim sought by the Lee group through its "human rights" ruckus to defile the dignified system of the DPRK, bring the inter-Korean relations back to those in the era of confrontation and do harm to the DPRK in collusion with foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-mentioned campaign kicked off by the Lee group in league with outside forces has made it difficult to expect any progress in the inter-Korean relations or any advance in the movement for independent reunification.

Reception Given by Palestinian Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Palestinian Ambassador to the DPRK Mohammad Shahta Zarab hosted a reception at his embassy on Tuesday to commemorate the Day of the Sun and the 15th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea Choe Thae Bok, Minister of Public Health Choe Chang Sik, Chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea Kim Pyong Phal and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mohammad Shahta Zarab said at the reception that the friendly relations between the two countries provided by former President Yasser Arafat and President Kim Il Sung are developing under the deep care of chief Mahmoud Abbas and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Palestinian people are standing by the side of the Korean people in the struggle to get the U.S. troops withdrawn from south Korea and achieve the country's reunification while fully supporting all initiatives of the DPRK for national reunification, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador hoped that the friendly Korean people would achieve greater progress and prosperity, overcoming difficulties under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok said it is an expression of the Palestinian friends' boundless reverence for Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il that they have joined the Korean people in commemorating the significant holidays including the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the Korean people, in the future, too, would render full support and solidarity to the Palestine people in their just cause to retake the territory occupied by Israel and regain the legitimate national rights including the right to found an independent state with Kuds as its capital.

Foreigners Visit Revolutionary Site
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited the Kwanhakgol Revolutionary Site on Wednesday to mark the 15th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the corps went round the revolutionary relics there, including a historic dwelling house and a study site preserved as they were, being briefed on the fact that the leader had acquired character and qualities as the brilliant commander of Mt. Paektu, staying there during the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the visit they made an entry in the visitor's book. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Military Attache of the Cuban embassy Miguel Angel Gala Valiente wrote that he wishes the leader good health on the occasion of the anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chinese Military, Air and Naval Attache Sun Yanfeng said that the Korean people are the happiest people in the world as they are blessed with illustrious leaders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian Military Attache Alexei Bartusov wrote that he wishes the Korean people bigger success in building a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Papers Editorially Call for Exalting Dignity and Might of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Papers today dedicate editorials to the 15th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says that the election of Kim Jong Il to the top post of the National Defence Commission helped solve the most important issue of providing a guarantee for the destiny and future of the Workers' Party of Korea and the revolution, the country and the people in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is now demonstrating its might as a political and ideological power dynamically advancing along the road of socialism under the uplifted banner of independence despite any storm of the times and an invincible military power which no formidable enemy can dare provoke, the paper says, and goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The absolute trust and reverence for the headquarters of the revolution prevail throughout the country and all the servicepersons and people are confidently advancing toward the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation, united close around the leader. This stirring reality of the country is a clear proof of the justice and tremendous vitality of the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last 15 years during which Kim Jong Il has led the DPRK, shouldering upon himself the heavy responsibility of the chairman of the NDC shine as proud annals in which he has firmly defended the lifeline of the country and the revolution and ushered in a new era of prosperity with his great Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a miracle to be recorded in the human history of politics that he resolutely smashed the anti-DPRK moves of the imperialist allied forces and brought about a turning phase in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation during the unprecedentedly difficult periods of the "Arduous March," the forced march under the uplifted banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics of Kim Jong Il is great politics which helps create a history of invincibility by fully enlisting the mental power of all servicepersons and people, effective politics for powerfully demonstrating the dignity and might of the socialist country with matchless military power and serves as an all-powerful treasured sword for bringing an era of great creation and change to this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation is sure to triumph thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, the single-minded unity of all servicepersons and people closely rallied around the headquarters of the revolution and the solid foundation that has grown strong despite rigorous trials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson calls for more powerfully demonstrating the dignity and might of the DPRK and bringing about a fresh turn in building the great prosperous powerful socialist nation and accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Election as Chairman of NDC of DPRK Celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- A meeting of members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union was held at the plaza before the Tower of the Juche Idea on Tuesday to celebrate the 15th   anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting Chairwoman of the Central Committee of the KDWU Ro Song Sil delivered a report to be followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said that Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the NDC was a manifestation of all servicepersons and people's  absolute support to and trust in the great Songun brilliant commander and marked an event of epochal significance in the destiny of the country and the nation and in the future development of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted with pride that in the period in which the servicepersons and people of the DPRK have pushed forward the revolution and construction with the peerless illustrious commander born of Heaven at their head the dignity and national power of Songun Korea reached the highest level and this land greeted a heyday of grandeur and prosperity unprecedented in the national history spanning 5,000 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The poem devoted to this day "Let's Hold Songun Brilliant Commander of Mt. Paektu in Higher Esteem" was recited at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea Kim Jung Rin, officials of the KDWU and members of the KDWU in Pyongyang.

Peerlessly Brilliant Commander of DPRK, Invincible Military Power
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Today the Korean army and people are significantly celebrating the 15th anniversary of the election of General Secretary Kim Jong Il as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is entirely thanks to his wise leadership that the DPRK is bringing about epoch-making changes, displaying its might as a matchlessly powerful nation and unbreakable fortress of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With deep insight into the changed international situation and the requirement of the Korean revolution in the 1990s, he formulated the Songun politics as the main mode of socialist politics by which the People's Army is taken as the pillar of the revolution and the overall socialist cause is pushed forward in reliance upon it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, shouldering the heavy responsibility of the chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission in the unprecedentedly grave period when the destiny of the country and the nation was at stake, thoroughly applied the Songun politics to all the realms of the state construction and activities, thus strengthening the politico-military power of the DPRK and advancing the cause of Korean-style socialist construction along the road of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatest exploit performed by him was that he increased the military power of the country incomparably and consolidated the military position of the Korean revolution as firm as rock through brilliant embodiment of the Juche-oriented idea on the construction of national defence and line on the building of revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He defined the military power as the foremost national power and the consolidation of the military position of the revolution as the primary task in the state construction and activities, and expounded the truth of the great Songun that the army is precisely the Party, state and people. And he concentrated all efforts on training the People's Army, the backbone and pillar of the self-reliant national defence power, to be a matchlessly invincible revolutionary army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has prepared the whole of the People's Army as units of human bullets and bombs ready to lay down their lives in protecting the leader and a-match-for-a hundred fighters through the vigorous movement to win the title of O Jung Hup-led Seventh Regiment. He has led wisely the work to rapidly renovate the military and technical hardware of the army to effect a great turn in strengthening the revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He showed love for and trust in servicepersons and provided all conditions for perfecting the combat preparation while making a continued inspection to army units. His patriotic long journey for Songun was the greatest motive power which reared the People's Army as the strong revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu, the first death-defying corps for protecting socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth the revolutionary line of giving precedence to the national defence industry and led its thorough implementation so as to develop the national defence industry into powerful one based on the latest achievements of science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il has consolidated the military position of the Korean revolution as an impregnable fortress that any formidable enemy can not break and arranged a strong and self-reliant war deterrent power and thus turned the DPRK into an invincible military power. His Songun revolutionary exploits will shine long down through history.

Attraction and Vitality of Juche Idea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The Juche idea has been disseminated worldwide century after century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung and developed and enriched by General Secretary Kim Jong Il is the recognized international trend in the era of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The key point of the idea is that the popular masses are the master of revolution and construction and they have the strength to propel them. In other word, man is the master of his destiny and he has the ability to shape it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The truth, scientific accuracy and justness of the Juche idea, man-centered world outlook have been irrefutably proven in the course of the development of history and revolutionary practices and the desire of the progressive people around the world to study the Juche idea is growing intense day by day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In response to the requirement of the times, the international scientific symposium on the Juche idea held in September Juche 65 (1976) in the Capital of Madagascar put forward the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and its application as a common work of the world and stressed the need to found an international academic institution for its further development and specified this in its declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On April 9, 1978, the grand inaugural meeting of the International Institute of the Juche idea took place in Tokyo, Japan, in compliance with the unanimous will and demand of the adherents to the idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The founding of the institute brought into being a core base for organized and purposeful activities for the study and  propagation of the Juche idea worldwide, making the idea a global theory beyond the boundary of its mother country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now, beside the institute, more than 1 100 organizations for the study of the Juche idea are active in 100 odd countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It shows that the Juche idea is the source of invincible strength inspiring the progressives with courage and confidence in the victory of the global cause of independence and its attraction and vitality are growing day by day.

